tip.text: The portions are really small. Only about 1/4 of the bowl size. Pathetic!
This is a neat 100% vegan bakery and cafe in Taiwan. Read the wonderful review of it here: http://www.messyvegetariancook.com/2014/12/09/vegan-heaven-in-taiwan-jiaoxi-vegan-bakery/
If you like baked eggs, try the shakshuka (RM20). A hearty North African egg dish, Copper's version is made with chicken chorizo and zucchini infused with basil, served in a tangy stewed tomato base.
The Brussels waffle looks really interesting and delectableas featured on Unique Sweets TV show.
You can find roasted coconuts here. Roasted coconuts are good for reducing wind and digestion problems. Additionally, coconut pudding that contains milk is available. Featured in Taste with Jason.
Currently, this is the first and only Sangkaya shopping mall retail outlet that was opened in November 2014.

tip.text: Flavours of their dairy-free ice creams include: Del Lago Chocolate,  Peanut Butter Fudge Mash, Sicilian Hazelnut Truffle, New Orleans Salted Praline, Alphonso Mango, Key Lime Creme and Mint Almond.
DF Mavens serves some of the finest 100% non-dairy ice cream / frozen desserts. Their menu boast an array of “Grab and Go” beverages and food, teas, juices, soups, ice Cream, shakes & frozen bars
Pinch of Salt membership card for 10% rebate at TGIF.
They have Argentine sea prawns to Spanish Iberico pork, Irish oysters & John Ross Jr Scottish smoked salmon to Korean sea eel available here but do call to confirm.
Apparently the mole sauce could be made out of 100 ingredients. Illiana says forget what you know about Mexican food because it is natural, lots of vegetables and fresh.
This place was featured in The Star on 17th November 2014. Mentioned that parts of the Iberico vegetarian pig could even be eaten raw due to its diet!

I am sure (in fact, I am very sure) this is one of the few restaurants in Klang Valley that has a variable spiciness/heat levels for their buffalo wings. This is the way that buffalo wings should be!
